data.description: Do not miss this truly special home. Built in 1935, this classic brick Colonial has character at every turn. Enter the center hall and step down on the left into the living room with a marble fireplace and ample room for entertaining. Continue to the glass-enclosed side porch with access to the rear brick patio and views of the front and side yards. Turn to the right from the center hall into the large dining room. Beautiful built-in cabinets adorn two corners of the room. The eat-in kitchen is at the back of the home, adjacent to the dining room. Across the hall, you will find a room used as a home office. A half bath and pantry closet are located at the end of the hall. Access the rear yard through a small mudroom. Moving to the second floor, you will find the large primary bedroom with a full bathroom. Two other sizable bedrooms, the main bathroom, a walk-in closet, and a cedar closet complete the second floor. The third floor is an exceptionally large room that was, at one time, divided into two bedrooms. Hardwood floors throughout the house except for the kitchen and bathrooms. The full basement is finished on one side with a pool table and a small counter/bar with a sink and cabinets. The other side is for laundry, storage, and utilities. A shed for additional storage and a driveway for parking up to four cars is located around the bend. The front of the home has unobstructed views of open municipal land. This is a one-of-a-kind home. Schedule your tour now.
